arts.ttl: Millwall boss address Macaulay Langstaff squad absence and some transfer window signings falling into ‘different category’
arts.sum: Alex Neil says that some of the younger players that Millwall signed in the winter transfer window are not first-team ready yet. “The difficulty I have got with Zak is that he has played limited football.

arts.ttl: Millwall boss: It was important we produced positive reaction to ‘bad’ loss at Plymouth Argyle
arts.sum: “It was important after a bad defeat – the manner in which it happened – did not become anything more than that, if that makes sense? Neil, while frustrated that other chances were not taken to take maximum points, could see far more to like from the display today than a shock heavy loss in Devon.

arts.ttl: Millwall boss Neil: Five-minute spell proved so costly - we should have beaten West Brom
arts.sum: Millwall produced a strong opening 25 minutes of front-footed play, so West Brom’s equaliser came as a shock. Alex Neil was left to rue a five-minute first-half spell in Millwall’s 1-1 home draw against West Bromwich Albion today at The Den.

arts.ttl: A brilliant day – Ipswich boss Kieran McKenna lauds debutant keeper Alex Palmer
arts.sum: The 28-year-old helped his side hold on for a point at Aston Villa.

arts.ttl: Debutant keeper Alex Palmer inspires 10-man Ipswich to valuable draw at Villa
arts.sum: Palmer pulled off a string of saves to frustrate the hosts.

arts.ttl: Unlucky Joe Bryan scores second own goal of the week as Millwall draw
arts.sum: Bryan had also put through his own net to open the scoring in the Lions’ 5-1 thrashing at Plymouth on Wednesday night.

arts.ttl: West Brom will soon unleash wildcard who 'wants Tony Mowbray to shout at him'
arts.sum: Bany was unveiled to the Albion supporters ahead of the victory over Sheffield Wednesday at The Hawthorns last Saturday and, while there is no time pressure to integrate him into the first-team squad, Tony Mowbray has a positive first impression of the 21-year-old, who he says 'wants the coach to shout at him' in order to demand more. "He's like a number ten, he wants to have the ball," Mowbray said.

arts.ttl: Tony Mowbray makes West Brom promise to 'really exciting' Tottenham star Will Lankshear
arts.sum: Tony Mowbray likes what he has seen so far from Will Lankshear in a West Bromwich Albion shirt so far, as the young loanee pushes for a first start when the Baggies face Millwall in need of a response on Saturday (kick off 3pm). Tony Mowbray greenlit a loan move for Tottenham Hotspur striker Will Lankshear before West Brom's transfer window ended

arts.ttl: West Brom boss expects fired-up Millwall side following ‘convincing’ Plymouth defeat
arts.sum: West Brom boss Tony Mowbray has stated he expects an exciting game as his side visits the Den for their Championship clash tomorrow. The Lions enter the match after a 5-1 humbling at the hands of Plymouth Argyle, who were dead last in the Championship going into the game.
